Description: Fragment of strap handle of a pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay medium, burnt; mixed inclusions. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 102, 14? 2011,5004.58 is an alternative candidate for the identification. Similar to Boerker and Burow, Die Hellenistichen Amphorenstempel aus Pergamon (Berlin 1998) nos. 693-4
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1573)
